ackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rdi1665702753224.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rdi1665702753224.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rdi1665702753224.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rdi1665702753224\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n /mwr \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rdi1665702753224___mwr_487294\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the type of middleware used for call-out or call-in when importing or exporting of interface definitions.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__topic_d150353e1_d150354e1_d150355e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__p_d150356e1_d150357e1_d150358e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/mwr=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MiddlewareType</var> { <var class=\"keyword varname\">OptionalMiddlewareSubswitches</var> }</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__topic_d108252e1_d108253e1_d108254e1_d108255e1_d108256e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d922137e68\">\n                  \n Used With\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52223e1_d52224e1_d52225e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"khj1665702753156.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/khj1665702753156.html\" title=\"Import interface definitions to integrate call-out to web services, various types of middleware, or to generate C call-in stub code for all types of components.\">/sti</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52226e1_d52227e1_d52228e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"grk1665702753295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/grk1665702753295.html\" title=\"Export interface definitions to integrate call-in from various types of middleware, or generate Java files for Java call-in, or generate C call-out stub code.\">/sto</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__topic_d108257e1_d108258e1_d108259e1_d108260e1_d108261e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d922137e97\">\n                  \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52229e1_d52230e1_d52231e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__p_d150365e1_d150366e1_d150367e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MiddlewareType</var>—one of the following values:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52232e1_d52233e1_d52234e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ws</code>—Web service definitions (WSDL). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dtg1665702543353.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dtg1665702543353.html\" title=\"Importing a WSDL file creates a Uniface signature for the web service so that Uniface components can activate operations on the web service. Use the command line command /sti /mwr=ws WSDL (the WSDL import facility) to import the file.\">Importing WSDL Definitions for Web Services</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ter1665702547737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ter1665702547737.html\" title=\"The WSDL export facility creates WSDL and XSD files from Uniface signatures. These files are used by web service requesters to call the web service.\">Exporting WSDL and Schema Files for Web Services Call-In</a>.\n                       </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52235e1_d52236e1_d52237e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">com</code>—COM type libraries\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52238e1_d52239e1_d52240e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__p_d150368e1_d150369e1_d150370e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OptionalMiddlewareSubswitches</var>:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52241e1_d52242e1_d52243e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ibg1665702754358.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ibg1665702754358.html\" title=\"Import a Document/Literal WSDL file using the Document/Literal Bare binding style.\">/bare</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52244e1_d52245e1_d52246e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zcq1719661703205.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zcq1719661703205.html\" title=\"Create entities and models.\">/dataonly</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52247e1_d52248e1_d52249e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pki1665702753074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pki1665702753074.html\" title=\"Generate sample XML, which describes what is required for each complex parameter, or where possible, generate modeled entities for complex data.\">/gen</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52250e1_d52251e1_d52252e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ber1665702754637.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ber1665702754637.html\" title=\"Specifies a model name for Uniface objects that are added when importing WSDL definitions for call-out.\">/mod</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52253e1_d52254e1_d52255e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rmr1719655329263.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rmr1719655329263.html\" title=\"Checks syntax only. No signatures, entities, or occurrences are updated or added.\">/nosig</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52256e1_d52257e1_d52258e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"btn1719662880134.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btn1719662880134.html\" title=\"Specifies a type library to be loaded into Uniface.\">/pid</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52259e1_d52260e1_d52261e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vve1665702753500.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vve1665702753500.html\" title=\"Specify the path name for generation of Java files for Java call-in, or for stub-code generation for C call-in and C call-out..\">/pth</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__li_d52262e1_d52263e1_d52264e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dic1665702754781.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dic1665702754781.html\" title=\"Display parse tree and messages.\">/verbose</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__topic_d108262e1_d108263e1_d108264e1_d108265e1_d108266e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d922137e243\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rdi1665702753224__p_d150374e1_d150375e1_d150376e1\">The <var class=\"keyword varname\">MiddlewareType</var> determines the additional switches and parameters that can be specified when importing with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sti</span> and exporting with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sto</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/mwr Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /mwr Specify the type of middleware used for call-out or call-in when importing or exporting of interface definitions. /mwr= MiddlewareType { OptionalMiddlewareSubswitches } Used With /sti /sto Parameters MiddlewareType —one of the following values: ws —Web service definitions (WSDL). For more information, see Importing WSDL Definitions for Web Services and Exporting WSDL and Schema Files for Web Services Call-In . com —COM type libraries OptionalMiddlewareSubswitches : /bare /dataonly /gen /mod /nosig /pid /pth /verbose Description The MiddlewareType determines the additional switches and parameters that can be specified when importing with /sti and exporting with /sto . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}